data.description: Welcome to this charming 3-bedroom, 1.5-bath home, a piece of history built in 1968, nestled on a coveted corner lot. Boasting a blend of vintage allure and modern updates, this property is an excellent canvas for your personal touch.    As you enter, you'll appreciate the absence of carpet, replaced with low-maintenance flooring throughout. The kitchen is a highlight, featuring granite countertops and original cabinets, offering a perfect balance of functionality and character. The main bathroom has been thoughtfully updated, seamlessly marrying contemporary elements with the home's classic charm.    Situated close to Randolph AFB, shopping, and entertainment, this property is not only a great starter home but also a promising investment opportunity. The absence of an HOA provides you with the freedom to customize and update the home to your liking.    Whether you're a first-time homebuyer looking for a cozy starter home or an investor seeking potential, this 1968 gem has something for everyone. With its prime location, updated main bathroom, and the opportunity for further enhancements, this property invites you to turn it into a space that reflects your style and vision. Don't miss out on the chance to make this house your home!
